            "ruleFormula": "[Sentence 1]. [Participial phrase], [Subject] [verb].\nA participial phrase at the start of a sentence (like 'Translated as…' or 'Running through the park…') must\nmodify the grammatical subject of that sentence. When two full thoughts are separated only by a comma, that\ncreates a comma splice. A period is the cleanest fix when the second sentence begins with such a modifying\nphrase.",
